5. python ELIF works on the idea of - as soon as conditions matches 
it will check the multiple conditions and execute the exact match.

age = 10

if age < 13:
  print("You are a child")
elif age < 20:
  print("You are a teenager")
elif age < 65:
  print("You are an adult")
elif age >= 65:
  print("You are a senior")

o/p= You are a child

6. shorthand if -
we can also use one-liner if statement
eg- 
x=14, y=12
max = x if x>y else y

syntax-
variable = value_if_true if condition else value_if_false

7. if we don't want to put any execution for particular condition , we can use PASS with IF ( means no actio needed)
age= 16
if age<18:
    PASS
else:
    print("acess granted")





